  "body": "From added logging of NodeData hashes I figured out there is memory leak:\r\n````\r\nINFO [02-09|14:24:22.150] Imported new chain segment               blocks=482  txs=1798  mgas=102.815 elapsed=3.722s    mgasps=27.617 number=841995 hash=57ad8dâ€¦de\r\nb0b9 batch=59194  age=4y1mo2w\r\nINFO [02-09|14:24:23.705] Memory                                   nodes=160606 hashes=36586922 alloc=4293672 sys=7703164 numGC=1326\r\nINFO [02-09|14:24:23.705] Database                                 size=2823323648 written=93224961\r\n````\r\n\r\nMost probably cause of the leak is that the `t.evictNodeFromHashMap` is invoked already after a node has been modified, so it is failing to clear up the hashes that existed before the modification. Will try to make the clearing up unconditional, to see if the leak goes away",
